      <caption>Extracted text displayed after OCR recognition</caption>
    </screenshot>
  </screenshots>
  <releases>
    <release version="0.1.5" type="stable" date="2026-05-25">
      <description>
        <p>Architectural milestone: modular core services, progressive loading feedback, and hardened resource security.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Modular Core Architecture: restructured application into specialized boot, i18n, and resource services.</li>
          <li>Progressive Loading: added granular status updates during OCR processing to eliminate Zombie UI.</li>
          <li>Offline Rotary Logging: implemented a secure, zero-telemetry local logging system with rotation.</li>
          <li>Resource Guards: added proactive memory monitoring to prevent OOM on high-resolution images.</li>
          <li>Worker Isolation: hardened OCR process isolation with transactional temporary directory management.</li>
          <li>Automated Cleanup: implemented native GObject destroy hooks for fail-safe resource management.</li>
          <li>Performance: introduced immutable dataclasses with optimized memory slots.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.1.4.3" type="stable" date="2026-05-16">
      <description>
        <p>Enhanced OCR preprocessing, modern keyboard shortcuts overlay, and robust screenshot fallback system.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Added advanced TextPreprocessor utility with intelligent image enhancement and OCR text cleanup.</li>
          <li>Added smart text preprocessing including common OCR error correction, whitespace normalization, and punctuation fixing.</li>
          <li>Added structured data extraction from OCR text (emails, URLs, phone numbers, dates).</li>
          <li>Added adaptive image enhancement based on brightness/contrast analysis for better OCR accuracy.</li>
          <li>Added modern ShortcutsOverlay widget with live search and categorized keyboard shortcuts.</li>
          <li>Added enhanced keyboard shortcuts overlay with search functionality and elegant Adw.Window-based interface.</li>
          <li>Added configurable logging level via ANURA_LOG_LEVEL environment variable for debugging.</li>
          <li>Added host screenshot fallback system using flatpak-spawn --host for missing portal backends.</li>
          <li>Added persistent install-hint banner when screenshot portal backend is missing.</li>
          <li>Added desktop-aware portal advice messages with environment-specific guidance.</li>
          <li>Added enhanced diagnostic logging for host screenshot operations.</li>
          <li>Added comprehensive drag-and-drop functionality with visual feedback and proper lifecycle management.</li>
          <li>Added complete drag-and-drop event handlers (enter, leave, motion, drop) with CSS styling for hover states.</li>
          <li>Added enhanced AboutDialog with complete legal information for Flathub compliance.</li>
          <li>Added full copyright and MIT license text for transparency.</li>
          <li>Added open source dependencies attribution in legal information.</li>
          <li>Added complete legal information ensuring Flathub compliance requirements.</li>
          <li>Added asynchronous Drag-and-Drop implementation to prevent UI freezes.</li>
          <li>Added fallback for URI list on clipboard texture read failure.</li>
          <li>Added optimized image thresholding using Look-Up Tables (LUT) for performance.</li>
          <li>Added enhanced accessibility and Micro-UX improvements for the OCR results page.</li>
          <li>Added persistent Drag-and-Drop controller for better stability.</li>
          <li>Fixed notification service cleanup and URI validator function calls.</li>
          <li>Fixed dialog response handling for browser launch failures.</li>
          <li>Fixed extra language combo signal connection and modal property removal.</li>
          <li>Fixed keyboard shortcuts test to match correct method signature.</li>
          <li>Fixed multiple UI/runtime bugs, memory leaks, and signal leaks.</li>
          <li>Fixed X11 Drag-and-Drop deadlocks and portal file transfer freezes.</li>
          <li>Fixed TTS state transitions, visual feedback, and audio issues.</li>
          <li>Fixed localization initialization and updated Italian translations.</li>
          <li>Fixed broken status window in Legal Information page.</li>
          <li>Resolved GTK navigation warnings and linting violations.</li>
          <li>Fixed About dialog property names and legal information display.</li>
          <li>Improved error handling for browser launch and file filters.</li>
          <li>Fixed UI spinner animations and state management.</li>
          <li>Refactored Drag-and-Drop system for improved reliability.</li>
          <li>Optimized Flatpak build and updated dependencies.</li>
          <li>Improved OCR pipeline and image processing performance.</li>
          <li>Updated release notes generation logic with hybrid GitHub link display.</li>
          <li>Added clickable QR URL notifications via XDG Desktop Portal (Flatpak-safe).</li>
          <li>Added autocopy for QR-detected URLs with improved toast feedback.</li>
          <li>Added pattern-based file filters for image selection dialog.</li>
          <li>Added real-time word count status bar in OCR results page.</li>
          <li>Added standardized localization infrastructure and Application ID.</li>
          <li>Fixed path traversal vulnerability in LanguageManager.remove_language (HIGH severity).</li>
          <li>Fixed URL userinfo spoofing in uri_validator (security fix).</li>
          <li>Fixed URL truncation during QR code extraction and hand-off.</li>
          <li>Fixed clipboard infinite fallback loop on image read failures.</li>
          <li>Fixed callback exception handling in clipboard service.</li>
          <li>Fixed Gio.Notification API usage for XDG Portal compatibility.</li>
          <li>Fixed i18n bindings in Flatpak and globalized autocopy behavior.</li>
          <li>Fixed Flatpak hybrid UI regression (i18n).</li>
          <li>Fixed localization issues and cleaned up UI code.</li>
          <li>Fixed broken state warning on Acknowledgements page.</li>
          <li>Fixed navigation focus race condition.</li>
          <li>Removed compiled gresource from git tracking and updated .gitignore.</li>
          <li>Fixed line length violation in notification service tests.</li>
          <li>Conducted deep codebase audit and concurrency hardening across all services.</li>
          <li>Pre-compiled regex patterns and optimized PIL thresholding for performance.</li>
          <li>Optimized URI validation performance with compiled regex.</li>
          <li>Optimized image enhancement pipeline and QR code detection.</li>
          <li>Performed full i18n audit and fixed hardcoded UI strings across the application.</li>
          <li>Stabilized i18n infrastructure and synchronized translations (Phase 1A/1B).</li>
          <li>Finalized Italian localization with navigation focus fixes.</li>
          <li>Improved Palette UX and accessibility across ExtractedPage.</li>
          <li>Refactored language API, removed dead code, and improved test coverage.</li>
          <li>Standardized loading spinner size across the application.</li>
          <li>Updated testing documentation.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.1.4.2" type="stable" date="2026-05-05">
      <description>
        <p>Hardened thread safety, sanitized error logging, and optimized resource cleanup.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Fixed `__slots__` conflict in ClipboardService - missing `_cancellable` in declaration causing AttributeError.</li>
          <li>Fixed ruff linting errors across codebase including import sorting and code style issues.</li>
          <li>Fixed concurrency issues in TTS and clipboard services against race conditions.</li>
          <li>Fixed memory leaks and added structural robustness throughout application.</li>
          <li>Fixed API contract, thread safety, and race condition issues in core services.</li>
          <li>Fixed Flatpak manifest warnings by removing `_comment` properties.</li>
          <li>Extracted URI validation to utils module and relaxed IP/localhost restrictions.</li>
          <li>Improved code quality with comprehensive type hints and cleanup.</li>
          <li>Implemented atomic cancellation for Clipboard and thread-safe signal emission for TTS GStreamer bus.</li>
          <li>Enhanced thread safety patterns across all services.</li>
          <li>Added comprehensive unit tests for core services.</li>
          <li>Resolved all remaining linting errors and line length issues.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.1.4.1" type="stable" date="2026-05-02">
      <description>
        <p>Hotfix release for UI initialization issues and notification improvements.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Fixed missing Adw.init() call causing "greyed out UI" on some systems.</li>
          <li>Fixed GResource bundle loading to properly exit on failure instead of continuing with broken UI.</li>
          <li>Fixed notification portal API to use proper GLib.Variant format (a{sv}) for XDG Portal compatibility.</li>
          <li>Fixed notification import consistency with absolute imports throughout main.py.</li>
          <li>Fixed HTML escaping in release notes generation to prevent XSS vulnerabilities.</li>
          <li>Added CHANGELOG.md as source of truth for release notes.</li>
          <li>Added translate URL to metainfo for Weblate integration.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.1.4" type="stable" date="2026-05-01">
      <description>
        <p>Production release with critical bug fixes, security improvements, and Flathub compliance.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Fixed critical thread-safety issues and race conditions in language manager and screenshot service.</li>
          <li>Fixed memory leaks in widget lifecycle management and GStreamer bus watch.</li>
          <li>Fixed all Flatpak manifest dependencies (requests, urllib3, certifi, hatchling, pyzbar).</li>
          <li>Fixed blueprint compiler output directory for Flatpak builds.</li>
          <li>Fixed gresource bundle loading with correct UI file paths.</li>
          <li>Fixed filesystem permissions for Open Image and Drag &amp; Drop in sandbox.</li>
          <li>Fixed silent CLI mode to properly exit without opening UI window.</li>
          <li>Fixed CLI exit code to return 0 on success instead of 1.</li>
          <li>Fixed code quality issues: lint errors, import sorting, gettext shadowing.</li>
          <li>Fixed Telegram share URL to send text as message instead of URL.</li>
          <li>Updated OARS content rating for Flathub compliance.</li>
          <li>Improved CI/CD workflow with smoke tests and build verification.</li>
          <li>Updated tessdata-fast to pinned commit SHA for reproducible builds.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.1.3" type="stable" date="2026-04-25">
      <description>
        <p>Bug fixes and stability improvements.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Fixed import error in screenshot service (tessdata_config casing).</li>
          <li>Fixed missing init_tessdata() method in LanguageManager.</li>
          <li>Fixed settings module path mismatch (moved to anura/services/settings.py).</li>
          <li>Fixed blueprint-compiler GIRepository compatibility with GNOME Platform 49.</li>
          <li>Improved TTS cache file location (XDG_CACHE_HOME).</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
    <release version="0.1.0" type="stable" date="2026-04-23">
      <description>
        <p>Initial release of Anura (fork of Frog).</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Complete rebranding to Anura.</li>
          <li>Removed all telemetry and PostHog tracking for total privacy.</li>
          <li>Optimized sharing service: added X (formerly Twitter) and Instagram.</li>
          <li>Updated dependencies for modern Linux distributions.</li>
        </ul>
      </description>
    </release>
  </releases>
